-- EDP Renovaveis Signs 20-Year Power Purchase Agreement for U.S. Wind Farm
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2010-11-15T08:57:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/edp-renovaveis-signs-20-year-power-purchase-agreement-for-u-s-wind-farm.html
EDP Renovaveis SA, the renewable-
energy unit of Portuguese utility EDP-Energias de Portugal SA,
said it signed a 20-year power purchase agreement for a 99-
megawatt wind farm in the U.S. market.  The project is scheduled to be fully commissioned in 2011,
the unit of Lisbon-based EDP said today in a regulatory filing.
EDP Renovaveis said it expects to install 0.2 gigawatts of
capacity a year in 2011 and 2012.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joao Lima at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net  